<title>ISRAEL: Hapoalim to net $24 mln from sale.</title>
<headline>Hapoalim to net $24 mln from sale.</headline>
<dateline>TEL AVIV 1996-09-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Bank Hapoalim said the sale of Poalim Investment to Dovrat Shrem &amp; Co Ltd will contribute an estimated $24 million to the bank's net profit.</p>
<p>Last week Bank Hapoalim announced the approval of the sale of 50 percent of its holdings in its investment company to Dovrat Shrem for $63 million.</p>
<p>Dovrat Shrem made the highest offer in a tender for Poalim Investment, valuing the company at $277 million against a market value of $150 million.</p>
<p>The agreement conforms with Bank Hapoalim's requirement to reduce its holdings in non-financial companies in accordance with Israel's banking laws.</p>
<p>- Tel Aviv newsroom, 972-3-537-2211</p>
